==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[spillan]]''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|spills|spilling|'''[[spilled]] '''or''' [[spilt]]'''}}

#{{transitive}} To [[drop]] something so that it goes [[spread]]s out or makes a [[mess]]; to [[pour]].
#:''I '''spilled''' some sticky juice on the kitchen floor.''

===Translations===
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[läikyttää]]
{{bottom}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{countable}} A [[mess]] of something that has been dropped.
#A [[fall]] or [[stumble]].
#:''The bruise is from a bad spill he had last week.''

===See also===
*[[spillway]]
*[[take a spill]]

